WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.400
This is the Monterey Bay AI Lab, from start to finish.

00:00:04.400 --> 00:00:10.400
It is an autonomous science lab that turns hundreds of public ocean datasets into earlier

00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:12.400
honest warnings for coastal hazards.

00:00:12.400 --> 00:00:14.400
Here is the whole journey.

00:00:14.400 --> 00:00:16.142
Start with the problem.

00:00:16.142 --> 00:00:23.544
Coastlines face hazards that hurt people and close beaches: bacteria that make the water unsafe to swim

00:00:23.544 --> 00:00:28.333
harmful algal blooms that put the toxin domoic acid into seafood

00:00:28.333 --> 00:00:30.075
and low-oxygen dead zones.

00:00:30.075 --> 00:00:35.300
Communities need warnings that arrive earlier, and that they can actually trust.

00:00:35.300 --> 00:00:38.683
So the lab built a data lakehouse.

00:00:38.683 --> 00:00:44.000
It fetches hundreds of raw public sources: Argo floats, ocean observatories

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.350
satellite chlorophyll and sea-surface temperature, rainfall and weather forecasts

00:00:48.350 --> 00:00:50.767
river flow, and pollution feeds.

00:00:50.767 --> 00:00:56.083
Four hundred twenty-six sources and billions of rows are cleaned, named

00:00:56.083 --> 00:01:01.400
and governed into trustworthy silver tables before any model sees them.

00:01:01.400 --> 00:01:06.088
On top of the clean data run the discovery engines.

00:01:06.088 --> 00:01:10.306
Many model families compete: simple baselines, gradient-boosted trees, rankers

00:01:10.306 --> 00:01:14.525
neural sequence models, tensor factorizations, and zero-shot foundation models.

00:01:14.525 --> 00:01:18.275
No model is trusted because it is fancy.

00:01:18.275 --> 00:01:23.900
Each one has to earn its place against a fair, simpler comparison.

00:01:23.900 --> 00:01:27.559
This is the heart of the lab: the evidence gate.

00:01:27.559 --> 00:01:31.949
Before any experiment runs, the kill metrics are written down in advance.

00:01:31.949 --> 00:01:36.339
A candidate signal only survives if it clears every one of them.

00:01:36.339 --> 00:01:38.900
This is what keeps the lab honest.

00:01:38.900 --> 00:01:40.585
The gate is strict.

00:01:40.585 --> 00:01:44.375
A real signal has to beat its own baseline

00:01:44.375 --> 00:01:48.165
survive a permutation null where the answers are shuffled

00:01:48.165 --> 00:01:51.956
hold up under bootstrap confidence intervals that exclude zero

00:01:51.956 --> 00:01:56.167
and pass adversarial red-teams that actively try to break it.

00:01:56.167 --> 00:01:59.115
Ranking correlations by metadata is not evidence.

00:01:59.115 --> 00:02:00.800
Only the filter is.

00:02:00.800 --> 00:02:02.937
The result is a funnel.

00:02:02.937 --> 00:02:07.212
Hundreds of tempting candidate links go in at the top.

00:02:07.212 --> 00:02:10.204
Most collapse: shared climate trends, sampling effort

00:02:10.204 --> 00:02:12.769
or sensor smearing explain them away.

00:02:12.769 --> 00:02:17.471
Out of one cross-run audit of two hundred eighty-four candidate links

00:02:17.471 --> 00:02:19.180
zero survived as defensible.

00:02:19.180 --> 00:02:22.600
The handful that do survive are worth trusting.

00:02:22.600 --> 00:02:25.681
The lab even walks back its own wins.

00:02:25.681 --> 00:02:31.459
An early headline claimed a HAB model beat the standard forecast by about ten times.

00:02:31.459 --> 00:02:35.311
On inspection, that was a broken-baseline mirage, not real skill

00:02:35.311 --> 00:02:40.319
so it was retracted and written into the record as a rejected claim.

00:02:40.319 --> 00:02:43.400
Overclaims do not survive contact with the gate.

00:02:43.400 --> 00:02:45.996
Here is what did survive.

00:02:45.996 --> 00:02:48.072
A zero-shot coastal-bacteria ranker.

00:02:48.072 --> 00:02:51.706
A clean-to-dirty warning that catches surprise flips.

00:02:51.706 --> 00:02:54.821
Domoic-acid onset forecasting for harmful blooms.

00:02:54.821 --> 00:02:56.379
Gulf hypoxia flagging.

00:02:56.379 --> 00:03:01.051
Microcystin genotype results that replicated nationally and in Alberta.

00:03:01.051 --> 00:03:05.204
And a tsunami screen that cuts false alarms.

00:03:05.204 --> 00:03:07.800
Each one cleared the gate.

00:03:07.800 --> 00:03:11.400
And then came the newest headline: the Carrier-Timescale Law.

00:03:11.400 --> 00:03:13.400
It answers a portfolio-level question.

00:03:13.400 --> 00:03:18.600
When does paying for a weather forecast feed actually buy you earlier warning

00:03:18.600 --> 00:03:21.000
and when is it wasted money?

00:03:21.000 --> 00:03:26.465
The law says a forecast only extends lead time when three conditions all hold.

00:03:26.465 --> 00:03:31.929
One: the driver is fast and flashy, like rain, so yesterday's reading goes stale.

00:03:31.929 --> 00:03:35.832
Two: there is real headroom over what you already observe.

00:03:35.832 --> 00:03:40.126
Three: the regional forecast is accurate enough to cash that headroom.

00:03:40.126 --> 00:03:42.858
Two out of three is a null.

00:03:42.858 --> 00:03:45.200
All three is a deployable advisory.

00:03:45.200 --> 00:03:46.940
That yields a real

00:03:46.940 --> 00:03:54.337
shippable product: a two-day-ahead beach bacteria exceedance advisory that runs on a free public NOAA forecast feed.

00:03:54.337 --> 00:03:56.077
It is deliberately scoped.

00:03:56.077 --> 00:03:59.123
It is a two-day advisory, not three.

00:03:59.123 --> 00:04:02.604
It is for densely sampled marine enterococcus beaches.

00:04:02.604 --> 00:04:04.779
The effect sizes are modest.

00:04:04.779 --> 00:04:10.000
The strength is discipline and portability, not a giant jump in accuracy.

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:12.048
The portability is the surprise.

00:04:12.048 --> 00:04:17.374
The advisory was trained on California and New Jersey with zero local labels

00:04:17.374 --> 00:04:23.929
then it deployed cold-start onto brand-new networks it had never seen: New South Wales in Australia

00:04:23.929 --> 00:04:25.977
and the Texas Gulf coast.

00:04:25.977 --> 00:04:26.797
On both

00:04:26.797 --> 00:04:31.713
the free forecast feature was load-bearing and beat the local recurrence baseline.

00:04:31.713 --> 00:04:35.400
Two independent networks, so it is not a fluke.

00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:37.177
There is one more gift.

00:04:37.177 --> 00:04:38.243
A free pre-screen.

00:04:38.243 --> 00:04:41.796
Using only observed data and no forecast fetch at all

00:04:41.796 --> 00:04:48.193
the lab can tell you in advance whether a forecast feed will pay off at a given beach.

00:04:48.193 --> 00:04:50.325
The master gate is oracle headroom.

00:04:50.325 --> 00:04:55.300
It turns a one-off product into a portfolio tool for deciding where to invest.

00:04:55.300 --> 00:04:59.300
All of this lives on a public Mission Control site.

00:04:59.300 --> 00:05:02.900
It shows what data exists, which models were built

00:05:02.900 --> 00:05:08.100
and what has actually been learned, including the nulls and the walked-back claims.

00:05:08.100 --> 00:05:10.900
Raw data downloads are deliberately turned off.

00:05:10.900 --> 00:05:14.500
The site publishes the science, not the private inputs.

00:05:14.500 --> 00:05:18.636
That is the Monterey Bay AI Lab, start to finish.

00:05:18.636 --> 00:05:21.532
Hundreds of public datasets, many competing models

00:05:21.532 --> 00:05:28.150
and a relentless evidence gate that turns noise into a small number of warnings worth trusting.

00:05:28.150 --> 00:05:30.632
The honesty is not a footnote.

00:05:30.632 --> 00:05:32.700
It is the whole point.
